newsitem.title: EGYPT: Egyptian pound overnight, one-week rates fall. [CORRECTED 13:45 GMT]
newsitem.headline: Egyptian pound overnight, one-week rates fall. [CORRECTED 13:45 GMT]

text.p: Overnight interbank rates on the pound fell on Thursday in a liquid end-of-week market, with private sector bankers quoting rates of between 9 and 9 1/2 percent against Wednesday's range of 9 3/4 and 10 1/8. (Corrects Wednesday's range)
Some bankers said overnight rates were at 9 15/16. One-week rates were also lower at between 9 1/2 and 9 3/4 from Wednesday's 9 3/4 and 10 1/8 percent.
"They've all broken the 10 percent barrier. It's Thursday and as usual there's a lot of money ahead of the weekend," one banker said.
State-owned banks kept their minimum lending rate at 10 1/2 percent.
